<p>
I recently came across the idea of an '100 List' (<a href="https://www.alexmolas.com/100-list">on this blog</a>, which referenced being inspired by <a href="https://huyenchip.com/list-100/">this blog</a>). 
Which I suppose is basically just a bucket list. I like the idea though, and I liked that there was a mix of difficulties of things on these lists.
As well as things that are large long term goals, there were also items that are small, but add to someones life in a way that is important to them.
This got me inspired to write my own. And by inspired, I mean I went and did it! By inspired I also mean, I knicked a bunch of ideas from these lists.
I'm 26 at time of writing these, so I didn't want to include too many things I've already done (that feels like cheating) but what
follows is a list of things I'd like to do at some point in my life. I did include one I'd already done (run a marathon) because I think that's the main thing
I've done that felt like a bucket list kind of achievement. I'll try keep updating this page as I think of more, as well as updating my progress as I go.
</p><br>
